<recipes>
    <recipe id="1">
        <recipeTitle>Jollibee Chickenjoy</recipeTitle>
        <ingredients>
            <ingredient>1 kg chicken, cut into pieces</ingredient>
            <ingredient>2 cups all-purpose flour</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 cup cornstarch</ingredient>
            <ingredient>2 tbsp garlic powder</ingredient>
            <ingredient>2 tbsp onion powder</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 tbsp paprika</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 tbsp salt</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 tbsp ground black pepper</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 cup buttermilk</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 egg</ingredient>
            <ingredient>Cooking oil for frying</ingredient>
        </ingredients>
        <cookingInstructions>In a bowl, mix buttermilk and egg. Soak chicken pieces for 3 hours. In a separate bowl, combine flour, cornstarch, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, salt, and black pepper. Coat each chicken piece in the dry mixture, then deep fry in hot oil at 350°F (175°C) until golden brown and crispy. Lastly, drain excess oil and serve hot.</cookingInstructions>
    </recipe>

    <recipe id="2">
        <recipeTitle>Jollibee Jolly Spaghetti</recipeTitle>
        <ingredients>
            <ingredient>500g spaghetti noodles</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 kg ground pork</ingredient>
            <ingredient>2 cups banana ketchup</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 cup tomato sauce</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 cup evaporated milk</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 cup sugar</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 cup hotdog slices</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 onion, chopped</ingredient>
            <ingredient>4 cloves garlic, minced</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 tbsp salt</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 tbsp ground black pepper</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 cup grated cheese</ingredient>
        </ingredients>
        <cookingInstructions>Cook spaghetti noodles according to package instructions, then set aside. In a pan, sauté garlic and onion, then add ground pork and cook until browned. Add hotdogs, banana ketchup, tomato sauce, sugar, evaporated milk, salt, and pepper. Simmer for 10 minutes. Lastly, pour sauce over cooked spaghetti and top with grated cheese.</cookingInstructions>
    </recipe>

    <recipe id="3">
        <recipeTitle>Jollibee Burger Steak</recipeTitle>
        <ingredients>
            <ingredient>500g ground beef</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/4 cup breadcrumbs</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 egg</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 tbsp soy sauce</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 tsp salt</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 tsp black pepper</ingredient>
            <ingredient>2 tbsp butter</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 cup sliced mushrooms</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 cup beef broth</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 tbsp cornstarch dissolved in 1 tbsp water</ingredient>
        </ingredients>
        <cookingInstructions>Mix ground beef, breadcrumbs, egg, soy sauce, salt, and pepper. Form into patties and pan-fry until cooked. In the same pan, melt butter and sauté mushrooms. Add beef broth and cornstarch mixture, then stir until thickened. Lastly, pour gravy over burger patties and serve hot.</cookingInstructions>
    </recipe>

    <recipe id="4">
        <recipeTitle>Jollibee Peach Mango Pie</recipeTitle>
        <ingredients>
            <ingredient>2 cups ripe mangoes, diced</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 cup canned peaches, chopped</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/4 cup sugar</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 tbsp cornstarch</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 tsp vanilla extract</ingredient>
            <ingredient>8 store-bought pastry sheets</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1 egg, beaten</ingredient>
            <ingredient>Cooking oil for frying</ingredient>
        </ingredients>
        <cookingInstructions>In a saucepan, cook mangoes, peaches, sugar, and vanilla over medium heat. Add cornstarch to thicken, then let cool. Spoon filling onto pastry sheets, fold into a pocket, and seal edges. Brush with egg wash. Lastly, deep fry until golden brown and serve warm.</cookingInstructions>
    </recipe>

    <recipe id="5">
        <recipeTitle>Jollibee Jolly Hotdog</recipeTitle>
        <ingredients>
            <ingredient>4 jumbo hotdogs</ingredient>
            <ingredient>4 hotdog buns</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 cup banana ketchup</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 cup mayonnaise</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/2 cup grated cheese</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/4 cup minced onions</ingredient>
            <ingredient>1/4 cup sweet pickle relish</ingredient>
        </ingredients>
        <cookingInstructions>Grill or pan-fry hotdogs until cooked. Place each hotdog in a bun. Top with banana ketchup, mayonnaise, grated cheese, onions, and sweet pickle relish. Lastly, serve warm and enjoy.</cookingInstructions>
    </recipe>
</recipes>
